 597:				; Calculate physical extent. Adapted from
 598:				; https://www.seasip.info/Cpm/format22.html:
 599:				; An extent is the portion of a file controlled by one directory entry. If a
 600:				; file takes up more blocks than can be listed in one directory entry, it is
 601:				; given multiple entries, distinguished by their EX and S2 bytes.  A logical
 602:				; extent is always 16 KB long, but there can be multiple logical extents in a
 603:				; physical extent (directory entry). This is defined by DPB.EXM. The formula
 604:				; is: directory number (physical extent) = ((32 * S2) + EX) / (exm + 1) where
 605:				; EXM is the extent mask value from the Disc Parameter Block.
